                    <span>In its usual way schaum's series gives out another book which is both helpful yet concise. This book gives the essential grounding for combinatorics and graph theory without being overly gargantuan encyclopedia..ample problems set the tone for a future mathematician. they  could've done better though..hence not the perfect 5 !</span>
                  
              
